module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Increasingly, people seem to misinterpret complexity as \nsophistication, which is baffling --- the incomprehensible should cause \nsuspicion rather than admiration.&nbsp;<br>\n<cite>-- Niklaus Wirth</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">... the cost of adding a feature isn't just the time it takes to \ncode it. The cost also includes the addition of an obstacle to future expansion. \n... The trick is to pick the features that don't fight each other. <cite><br>\n-- John Carmack</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">One of the most dangerous (and evil) things ever injected into \nthe project world is the notion of process maturity. Process maturity is for \nreplicable manufacturing contexts. Projects are one-time shots. Replicability is \nnever the primary issue on one-time shots. More evil than good has come from the \nnotion that we should &quot;stick to the methodology.&quot; This is a recipe for \nnon-adaptive death. I'd rather die by commission. <cite><br>\n-- David Schmaltz</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p> Every good work of software starts by scratching a developer's personal itch<br> <em>--<a href=\"http://www.firstmonday.org/issues/issue3_3/raymond\" target=\"_blank\"> \r\n  source</a></em></p>\r\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Refactoring provides enough energy to a system for it to relax \r\ninto a new and more comfortable state, a new local minimum. <br>\r\n-- <cite>Kevlin Henney</cite>, <i>\"The Imperial Clothing Crisis\" (2002) </i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \r\n  source</a>]</em></p>\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">The difference between a good and a poor architect is that the \npoor architect succumbs to every temptation and the good one resists it. <cite>\n<br>\n-- Ludwig Wittgenstein</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Beauty is more important in computing than anywhere else in \ntechnology because software is so complicated. Beauty is the ultimate defense \nagainst complexity. <cite><br>\n-- David Gelernter, </cite><i>&quot;Machine Beauty&quot;, Basic Books (1998)</i> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Fools ignore complexity; pragmatists suffer it; experts avoid \nit; geniuses remove it. <cite><br>\n-- Alan Perlis</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Any intelligent fool can make things bigger, more complex, and \nmore violent. It takes a touch of genius - and a lot of courage - to move in the \nopposite direction. <cite><br>\n-- Albert Einstein</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">...Simplifications have had a much greater long-range scientific \nimpact than individual feats of ingenuity. .... Simplicity and elegance are \nunpopular because they require hard work and discipline to achieve and education \nto be appreciated. <cite><br>\n-- Edsger W. Dijkstra</cite>&nbsp; <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Complexity is a sign of technical immaturity. Simplicity of use \nis the real sign of a well design product whether it is an ATM or a Patriot \nmissile. <cite><br>\n-- Daniel T. Ling</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">The unavoidable price of reliability is simplicity. <cite><br>\n-- C.A.R. Hoare</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p> Good programmers know what to write. Great ones know what to rewrite (and \r\n  reuse). <br>\r\n  <em>--<a href=\"http://www.firstmonday.org/issues/issue3_3/raymond\" target=\"_blank\"> \r\n  source</a></em></p>\r\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Simplicity does not precede complexity, but follows it. <cite>\n<br>\n-- Alan J. Perlis</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">The structure of a system reflects the structure of the \norganization that built it. <cite><br>\n-- R. Fairley</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Technical skill is mastery of complexity, while creativity is \nmastery of simplicity. <cite><br>\n-- E. Christopher Zeeman</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Architect: Someone who knows the difference between that which \ncould be done and that which should be done. <cite><br>\n-- Larry McVoy</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">If the automobile had followed the same development cycle as the \ncomputer, a Rolls-Royce would today cost $100, get a million miles per gallon, \nand explode once a year, killing everyone inside. <cite><br>\n-- Robert X. Cringely</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">There's an old story about the person who wished his computer \nwere as easy to use as his telephone. That wish has come true, since I no longer \nknow how to use my telephone. <cite><br>\n-- Bjarne Stroustrup</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">A common mistake that people make when trying to design \nsomething completely foolproof was to underestimate the ingenuity of complete \nfools. <cite><br>\n-- Douglas Adams</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">If our designs are failing due to the constant rain of changing \nrequirements, it is our designs that are at fault. We must somehow find a way to \nmake our designs resilient to such changes and protect them from rotting. <cite>\n<br>\n-- Robert C. Martin</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Controlling complexity is the essence of computer programming.\n<cite><br>\n-- Brian Kernighan</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">How good the design is doesn't matter near as much as whether \nthe design is getting better or worse. If it is getting better, day by day, I \ncan live with it forever. If it is getting worse, I will die. <cite><br>\n-- Kent Beck</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Nothing resolves design issues like an implementation. <cite>\n<br>\n-- J. D. Horton</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p> Perfection (in design) is achieved not when there is nothing more to add, \r\n  but rather when there is nothing more to take away<br>\r\n  <em>--Antoine de Saint-Exupery [<a href=\"http://www.firstmonday.org/issues/issue3_3/raymond\" target=\"_blank\"> \r\n  source</a>]</em></p>\r\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">By the time [the Leaning Tower of Pisa] was ten percent built, \neveryone knew it would be a total disaster. But the investment was so big they \nfelt compelled to go on. Since its completion, it cost a fortune to maintain and \nis still in danger of collapsing. There are no plans to replace it, since it was \nnever needed in the first place. I expect every installation has its own pet \nsoftware which is analogous to the above. <cite><br>\n-- Ken Iverson</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">If you lie to the compiler, it will get its revenge.<br>\n<i>--Henry Spencer</i> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">... the purpose of abstraction is not to be vague, but to create \r\na new semantic level in which one can be absolutely precise.<br>\r\n<cite>-- Edsger W. Dijkstra</cite>, <i>\"The Humble Programmer\" (1972) </i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \r\n  source</a>]</em></p>\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">In theory, there is no difference between theory and practice. \nBut, in practice, there is. <cite><br>\n-- Jan L. A. van de Snepscheut</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Trying to outsmart a compiler defeats much of the purpose of \nusing one.<br>\n<i>--Kernighan &amp; Plauger, The Elements of Programming Style</i> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "\r\nGet into a rut early: Do the same process the same way. Accumulate idioms. Standardize. The only difference(!) between Shakespeare and you was the size of his idiom list - not the size of his vocabulary. <br><i>--[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\" http://www.cs.yale.edu/quotes.html \">source</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Once a new technology starts rolling, if you're not part of the \nsteamroller, you're part of the road.<br>\n<i>--Stewart Brand </i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">There are two ways to write error-free programs; only the third \nworks.<br>\n<i>--Alan J. Perlis </i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Just because the standard provides a cliff in front of you, you \nare not necessarily required to jump off it. <br>\n<i>--Norman Diamond </i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "If you have a procedure with ten parameters, you probably missed some. <br><i>--[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\" http://www.cs.yale.edu/quotes.html \">source</a>]</i>";
module.exports = "<p> Any fool can write code that a computer can understand. Good programmers \r\nwrite code that humans can understand.<br>\r\n  <em>--Martin Fowler [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/redirect?link_code=as2&path=ASIN/0201485672&tag=anothedayinmy-20&camp=1789&creative=9325\"> \r\n  source</a>]</em></p>\r\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">I did say something along the lines of &quot;C makes it easy to shoot \nyourself in the foot; C++ makes it harder, but when you do, it blows your whole \nleg off.&quot; <br>\n<i>--Bjarne Stroustrup </i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">UNIX is simple. It just takes a genius to understand its \nsimplicity <br>\n<i>--Dennis Ritchie </i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">When someone says, &quot;I want a programming language in which I \nneed only say what I want done,&quot; give him a lollipop.<br>\n<i>--Alan Perlis </i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Einstein argued that there must be simplified explanations of \nnature, because God is not capricious or arbitrary. No such faith comforts the \nsoftware engineer.<br>\n<i>--Fred Brooks, Jr.</i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">You can't have great software without a great team, and most \nsoftware teams behave like dysfunctional families. <br>\n<i>--Jim McCarthy </i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">That's the thing about people who think they hate computers. \nWhat they really hate is lousy programmers.<br>\n<i>--Larry Niven and Jerry Pournelle Oath of Fealty </i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">As we said in the preface to the first edition, C &quot;wears well as \none's experience with it grows.&quot; With a decade more experience, we still feel \nthat way.<br>\n<i>--Brian Kernighan and Dennis Ritchie</i><em> [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "Optimization hinders evolution. <br><i>--[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\" http://www.cs.yale.edu/quotes.html \">source</a>]</i>";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">C++ tries to guard against Murphy, not Machiavelli.<br>\n<i>--Damian Conway</i><em> [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">I have always found that plans are useless, but planning is \nindispensable.<br>\n<i>--Dwight Eisenhower</i><em> [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p>Program testing can be used to show the presence of bugs, but never to show \r\ntheir absence! <br>\r\n  <em>--Edsger Dijkstra [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_testing\"> \r\n  source</a>]</em></p>";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">It is practically impossible to teach good programming style to \nstudents that have had prior exposure to Basic; as potential programmers they \nare mentally mutilated beyond hope of regeneration.<br>\n<i>--Edsger Dijkstra </i><em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Perl is another example of filling a tiny, short-term need, and \nthen being a real problem in the longer term.<br>\n<i>--Alan Kay</i><em> [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Comparing to another activity is useful if it helps you \nformulate questions, it's dangerous when you use it to justify answers.<br>\n<i>--Martin Fowler</i><em> [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "There will always be things we wish to say in our programs that in all known languages can only be said poorly. <br><i>--[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\" http://www.cs.yale.edu/quotes.html \">source</a>]</i>";
module.exports = "Every program is a part of some other program and rarely fits. \r\n<br><i>--[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\" http://www.cs.yale.edu/quotes.html \">source</a>]</i>\r\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">\r\n\r\nStyle distinguishes excellence from accomplishment. <br>\r\n<i>--James Coplien\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</em></i></p>";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">\r\n\r\nEvery program has (at least) two purposes: the one for which it was written, \r\nand another for which it wasn't.<br>\r\n<i>--Alan J. Perlis&nbsp;[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i></p>";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">\r\n\r\nTechnology is dominated by two types of people: Those who understand what they \r\ndo not manage. Those who manage what they do not understand.<br>\r\n<i>--Putt's Law&nbsp;[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i></p>";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">\r\n\r\nThe most amazing achievement of the computer software industry is its continuing \r\ncancellation of the steady and staggering gains made by the computer hardware \r\nindustry.<br>\r\n<i>--Henry Petroski&nbsp;[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i></p>";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">\r\n\r\nThe perfect project plan is possible if one first documents a list of all the \r\nunknowns.<br>\r\n<i>--Bill Langley&nbsp;[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eskimo.com/~hottub/software/programming_quotes.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i></p>";
module.exports = "<p> Testing is the process of comparing the invisible to the ambiguous, so as to \r\navoid the unthinkable happening to the anonymous. <br>\r\n  <em>--James Bach [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.satisfice.com/presentations/bste.pdf\"> \r\n  source</a>]</em></p>";
module.exports = "Java is, in many ways, C++--. \r\n<br><i>--Michael Feldman [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "There's no obfuscated Perl contest because it's pointless. <br>\r\n<i>--Jeff Polk [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>";
module.exports = "Software and cathedrals are much the same - first we build them, then we pray. \r\n<br><i>--Anonymous [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\nIf debugging is the process of removing bugs, then programming must be the process of putting them in. \r\n<br><i>--Edsger Dijkstra [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\nNo matter how slick the demo is in rehearsal, when you do it in front of a live audience the probability of a flawless presentation is inversely proportional to the number of people watching, raised to the power of the amount of money involved. \r\n<br><i>--Mark Gibbs [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n";
module.exports = "It is easier to write an incorrect program than understand a correct one. <br><i>--[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\" http://www.cs.yale.edu/quotes.html \">source</a>]</i>";
module.exports = "\r\nIf you need more than 3 levels of indentation, you're screwed anyway, and should fix your program. \r\n<br><i>--Linux 1.3.53 CodingStyle documentation [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\nSaying that Java is good because it works on all platforms is like saying anal sex is good because it works on all genders. \r\n<br><i>--Anonymous [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\nA Perl program is correct if it gets the job done before your boss fires you. <br><i>--Larry Wall [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\nI have a pretty major problem with a language where one of the most common variables has the name $_ \r\n<br><i>--Brian Hook, about PERL [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n";
module.exports = "The best way to get a project done faster is to start sooner\r\n<br>\r\n<em>--Jim Highsmith</em>";
module.exports = "<p> Beware of bugs in the above code; I have only proved it correct, not tried \r\nit . <br>\r\n  <em>--Knuth [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.brainyquote.com/quotes/authors/d/donald_knuth.html\"> \r\n  source</a>]</em></p>";
module.exports = "He who hasn't hacked assembly language as a youth has no heart. He who does as an adult has no brain. \r\n<br><i>--John Moore [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">Computer Science is the first engineering discipline in which \nthe complexity of the objects created is limited solely by the skill of the \ncreator, and not by the strength of raw materials. <cite><br>\n-- B. Reid</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\nThe evolution of languages: FORTRAN is a non-typed language. C is a weakly typed language. Ada is a strongly typed language. C++ is a strongly hyped language. \r\n<br><i>--Ron Sercely [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n";
module.exports = "<p align=\"left\">If you cannot grok the overall structure of a program while \ntaking a shower, you are not ready to code it. <cite><br>\n-- Richard Pattis</cite> <em>[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.jbox.dk/quotations.htm\"> \n  source</a>]</em></p>\n\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\n\r\nBASIC - A programming language. Related to certain social diseases in that those who have it will not admit it in polite company.\r\n<br><i>--Anonymous [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\n\r\nDon't get suckered in by the comments ... they can be terribly misleading. <br><i>--Dave Storer [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\n\r\nThe camel has evolved to be relatively self-sufficient. On the other hand, the camel has not evolved to smell good. Neither has Perl. \r\n<br><i>--Larry Wall [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n";
module.exports = "With enough eyes, all bugs are shallow. \r\n<br><i>--Eric S. Raymond [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We know about as much about software quality problems as they knew about the \r\nBlack Plague in the 1600s. We've seen the victims' agonies and helped burn the \r\ncorpses. We don't know what causes it; we don't really know if there is only one \r\ndisease. We just suffer -- and keep pouring our sewage into our water supply.\r\n<span class=\"author\"><br>\r\n<i>-- Tom Van Vleck</i></span><i> [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.multicians.org/thvv/proverbs.html\">source</a>]</i></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If something is worth doing once, it's worth building a tool to do it.<br>\r\n<i>--[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.multicians.org/thvv/proverbs.html\">source</a>]</i></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "<p> We try to solve the problem by rushing through the design process so that \n  enough time is left at the end of the project to uncover the errors that were \n  made because we rushed through the design process<br>\n  <em>--Glenford Myers [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.adrianmccarthy.com/blog/?p=15\"> source</a>]</em></p>\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\n\r\nI don't know or trust Demeter.\r\n<br><i>--David Brady [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.multicians.org/thvv/proverbs.html\">source</a>]</i>\r\n";
module.exports = "When we use a language, we should commit ourselves to knowing it, being able to read it, and writing it idiomatically.\r\n<br><i>--Ron Jeffries [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.multicians.org/thvv/proverbs.html\">source</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\nOne of the great skills in using any language is knowing what not to use, what not to say. ... There's that simplicity thing again.\r\n<br><i>--Ron Jeffries [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.multicians.org/thvv/proverbs.html\">source</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\nProgramming languages should be designed not by piling feature on top of feature, but by removing the weaknesses and restrictions that make additional features appear necessary.\r\n<br><i>-- Revised Report on the Algorithmic Language Scheme [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.multicians.org/thvv/proverbs.html\">source</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "Good engineering is characterized by gradual, stepwise refinement of products that yields increased performance under given constraints and with given resources. \r\n<br><i>--Niklaus Wirth [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\" http://www.adrianmccarthy.com/blog/?p=15\">source</a>]</i>\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\nIt should be noted that no ethically-trained software engineer would ever consent to write a DestroyBaghdad procedure. Basic professional ethics would instead require him to write a DestroyCity procedure, to which Baghdad could be given as a parameter.\r\n<br><i>--Nathaniel S. Borenstein[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.multicians.org/thvv/proverbs.html\">source</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\nA designer can mull over complicated designs for months. Then suddenly the simple, elegant, beautiful solution occurs to him. When it happens to you, it feels as if God is talking! And maybe He is.\r\n<br><i>--Leo Frankowski (in The Cross-Time Engineer) [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.multicians.org/thvv/proverbs.html\">source</a>]</i>\r\n\r\n";
module.exports = "If a million monkeys were typing on computers, one of them will eventually write a Java program. The rest of them will write Perl programs. \r\n<br><i>--Anonymous [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://r-101.blogspot.com/2006/09/top-50-programming-quotations.html\"> \r\nsource</a>]</i>";
module.exports = "\r\n\r\n\r\nThe problem with using C++ ... is that there's already a strong tendency in the language to require you to know everything before you can do anything.\r\n<br><i>--Larry Wall[<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.multicians.org/thvv/proverbs.html\">source</a>]</i>\r\n";
